I went there with my family Wednesday night. There were many empty tables when we got in. Then we told the waiter that we have 4 adults, 3 children and 1 infant total, the waiter replied the long tables were booked. And then we asked how long do we need to wait. He said it would be a long wait and he asked if we can sit separately. We thought about it and we thought it would be ok, because some kids might want to sit together at a small table. How ever, right after we said yes, the waiter told us “sorry, the stroller can’t go in”. My baby was asleep in the stroller, and he should have seen it right after we went in the restaurant. How cruel it is to wake up an asleep baby or leave the baby and stroll outside! I finally realized that he doesn’t want us to eat in the restaurant. The reason is so obvious: we have too many kids. I had been eating in the reasturant for more than 10 years, it broke my heart tonight. I don’t think I will go there for a long time. It’s so embarrassing to be ignored because of my own children.
